<BODY>
<H1>Who is Rob Weir?</H1><IMG alt=3D"Photo of Rob Weir" hspace=3D10=20
src=3D"http://www.robweir.com/blog/uploaded_images/rob.jpg" =
align=3Dleft>=20
<P>To the left is a recent picture of me at my sister's wedding. I used =
to look=20
<A href=3D"http://www.robweir.com/blog/attachments/farmer_rob.jpg">far =
more=20
technical</A> before that, having the requisite funny beard and =
pitchfork. And=20
yes, I do have a scythe.</P>
<P>I'm a 38 year-old hominid known to inhabit Westford, Massachusetts. I =
was=20
born in Athens, Greece of American parents, and grew up (mainly) in =
Saugerties,=20
New York. I am a 1991 graduate of Harvard College, with a degree in =
Astronomy=20
and Astrophysics. I am a member of the <A =
href=3D"http://www.stamps.org/">American=20
Philatelic Society</A>, the <A=20
href=3D"http://www.americantopicalassn.org/">American Topical =
Association</A>, the=20
<A href=3D"http://www.uschess.org/">United States Chess Federation</A>, =
the <A=20
href=3D"http://www.masschess.org/">Massachusetts Chess Association</A>, =
the <A=20
href=3D"http://www.masshort.org/">Massachusetts Horticultural =
Society</A>, the <A=20
href=3D"http://www.beertown.org/index.html">American Homebrewers =
Association</A>,=20
the <A href=3D"http://www.newenglandancestors.org/">New England Historic =

Genealogical Society</A>, the <A href=3D"http://www.acm.org/">ACM</A>, =
the <A=20
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/tc_home.php?wg_abbrev=3Doffi=
ce">OASIS=20
ODF TC</A> (Co-Chair), the <A=20
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/tc_home.php?wg_abbrev=3Dodf-=
adoption">OASIS=20
ODF Adoption TC</A>, <A href=3D"http://v1.incits.org/">INCITS V1</A> and =
a trained=20
<A href=3D"http://www.skywarn.org/">SkyWarn</A> weather spotter. I work =
for IBM,=20
as a performance architect, as well as on various ODF technical topics. =
In my=20
free time I grow and eat <A=20
href=3D"http://www.robweir.com/blog/2006/09/fruits-of-season.html">berrie=
s</A>. A=20
lot of them. </P>
<P>This is my personal blog. The postings on this site are my own and =
don't=20
necessarily represent the positions, strategies or opinions of any of =
the groups=20
or companies I'm associated with. I welcome comments, either on the =
blog, or=20
directly to me at <A =
href=3D"mailto:antic@robweir.com">antic@robweir.com</A> </P>
